    <briefdescription>
<para>Firmware image header — standardized format for OTA slots. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Each firmware slot (A or B) has this header at a known flash offset. The bootloader and OTA updater use it to decide which image to boot, whether an update succeeded, and when to rollback.</para>
<para>Layout in flash: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">[<ref refid="structSYN__FwImageHeader" kindref="compound">SYN_FwImageHeader</ref><sp/>(24<sp/>bytes)]<sp/>[firmware<sp/>binary<sp/>(image_size<sp/>bytes)]</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Lifecycle</title><para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para>OTA begins: header.state = WRITING</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>OTA complete: header.state = NEW (CRC verified)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>First boot: bootloader sets state = TESTING</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>App healthy: app calls confirm → state = CONFIRMED</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>App crashes: bootloader sees TESTING + unhealthy → state = INVALID, rollback </para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
